I live in a big city. My neighborhood is very mixed. Homes and stores are close together. There are many stores. Some are big, and some are small. There are many new restaurants. I like to walk to the stores and restaurants. There are also parks near my home. People take their children to the parks. There are many different kinds of people in my neighborhood. Some are gay, some are Jewish, and some are from Russia. There are other areas in the city with many people from different countries. For example, there is Korea Town, China Town, and Little Armenia. It is hard to drive in the city. Traffic is bad. People drive a lot. There are not many sidewalks. It is hard to find a place to park. The city is building many new apartments. People are moving to the city.

My neighborhood has many kinds of homes. Some are big buildings, and some are small houses. Some have one family, and some have two families. I do not know most of my neighbors. We are not close. I had many friends when I was a child. We played together.

My neighborhood is special. Many houses are for one family. Some houses are split into two, but still joined. My house has a small yard in front and a small drive on the side. It looks like houses from long ago when living in the suburbs was very popular. This dream used to make people happy.

Now, fewer people think this way. But my neighborhood still shows the dream is alive. People are not as happy as before. Yards are not as nice. But there are still cars in the drives. Kids play like the world is all they know.

The old school is still here. It is almost ninety years old. It shows hope to the young and remembers the past for older people. There are not many churches, but the basketball courts are full.

All the houses look different, but they feel the same. There is a big grocery store called Super "A". A big family from Yemen owns it. They are the only Arab family in the neighborhood. Most people are African American.

The streets are wide and kids play football. Cars stop for them. Many people have lived here for a long time. They know each other.

There used to be a karate school, but kids stopped going when karate movies were not popular. Now it is a medicine store.

There is a small movie theater. It shows old movies for less money. Young people do not like it, but older people do.

There is a big road that goes through town. It is not in our town exactly, but close. People wanted an exit in our town, but the older people said it would ruin things. 

They are building a new school and we are choosing a symbol for our town. I think a robot with a country accent and a small house would be a good symbol.

This area looks small and quiet. It is behind stores, not a place people think to live. But if you walk behind the old store and old hotels, you find a busy place. There are many apartment buildings here. They are close together, like toys inside each other.

The first buildings were in the news for bad things. We will not talk about those. The next buildings are different. They are a secret, known only to a few.  Across from these buildings is a small school. Students go there with coffee in the morning. They walk slow. Drivers get mad when they are late. The road goes to another place with a park and a hospital.

The hospital helps people who are hurt. It has chairs outside and a fan that moves the hot air. Children play in the park. They run and jump. Old people walk their dogs and watch the young people. They talk about their lives.

There is a place to buy food and things for pools. People can get a meal and buy pool stuff. There is also a place to buy frozen yogurt. Young people eat it while they ride their bikes and use special things that make smoke.

This area is a part of America. It is old and quiet. Not much changes here.

"Where is every thing?" she asked as we drove past the corn fields.  They filled the horizon. "This is it!" I said. I knew she would be surprised by the open space.  She was from a town where the store was a short walk away. She had never seen so much open land.

I told her about growing up in rural Ohio.  In that moment, she understood who I am and where I come from.  

We drove down a small road. We came to a lake. A small town is just past it. The houses are made of brick and stucco.  Each house has a lot of land. People take pride in keeping it nice. In the spring, there are many flowers. The trees change color in the fall. The driveways have expensive cars. They shine in the sun after a car wash.

My neighbor is Korean. He is always outside. He mows his lawn all day. He sings while he mows. Everyone laughs at him, but he is a good person. He had a long life and has lost some of his memory. He used to be a doctor.  He likes to mow his lawn with a John Deere mower.

You will come to my house. Geese are in the side yard. Our dog chases them. There is a small stream behind the house. You can hear bullfrogs, the stream, and cows from the farms nearby.

Across a wooden bridge is a quiet place. There are trees, plants, and flowers.  I spent much of my childhood there. I built tree houses and chased animals. There were always friends to play with.

Winter can be cold, but it is very beautiful. The yard changes from green to brown. The trees lose their leaves. When it snows, it looks like a winter wonderland. My sister and I made snow angels and snowmen. We fought a lot. In the winter, we used snowballs as weapons. We built forts to store our snowballs.

In our winter wonderland, we played pretend. It was a time when nothing else mattered. We were just kids.

Portland, Oregon has a special way. People say it is "weird". The city has a sign that says "Keep Portland Weird". Some people like this sign because it shows a time when Portland was smaller and more different.  Others think it means Portland is a good place to be different. Even though many rich people from California move to Portland, and there are many new buildings, Portland is still weird. 

"Weird" does not mean everyone is nice to each other. But it means people accept things that are not usual. Portland has modern things like stores from China.  There are many ways to be different. But Portland also has normal things like yoga, people who like to look stylish, and people who work in offices. 

Maybe "weird" means people in Portland do not take things too seriously. In my neighborhood, houses have bright colors. People grow flowers, fruits, and vegetables in their yards. There are boxes outside in the summer. These boxes have things people do not want anymore. Sometimes these boxes have clothes or books. Sometimes they have something special. It is fun to see what is inside.  

This is what Portland means to me. But there are many kinds of weird people in Portland.  Some people would never take clothes from a box on the street. These people do things like yoga with goats or watch soccer games. Portland has people who like many different things.  

Portland has some problems. Some people use drugs. This is often connected to mental health problems. The rain and clouds can make people feel sad.  There are also many homeless people. People in Portland want to help, but it is hard to know what to do.

The mountains are always there. They are in the north. They see the sun each morning and each evening. No matter how busy I am, they are there. They do not change. They do not care about problems. When I am stressed, I look at the mountains. They help me feel better. I came here for school. The mountains near the school were the first thing I liked. The school is pretty, with buildings, ponds, and trees. But the mountains are special. The town is also nice. There are many cafes where I studied. The center of town is old. The buildings are made of brick. It is busy there. But after a few blocks, the town is quiet again. This makes the town interesting. I have made many memories here. I have walked with friends in the park. I have seen movies in the theater. But there are sad memories too. The ponds are a good place to think. I have cried there when I felt lost. I watched the turtles and ducks. I wondered about my life. I walked past the pond, the park, and the houses. I reached a main street. The sun was shining. I saw the mountains. They were big and strong. They made me feel brave.

If you visit Bensonhurst in Brooklyn, it is easy to find. Public transport is good in New York City. Bensonhurst is a city neighborhood. You will see many Asian stores.

Many Asian people live in Bensonhurst now. You will see an Asian store almost every block. Supermarkets and laundry stores are popular. People like them because the food is good, the prices are low, and they are close.  Near where I live, there are four Asian supermarkets within two minutes of each other. This is very easy.

Bensonhurst is not only Asian. There are many different kinds of people. Many immigrants and their children live here. Most big stores are owned by Asians.

There is a new park nearby. It has basketball courts, a soccer field, handball courts, swings, and a playground. The park is diverse. Many different people play there. 

There are not many big offices in Bensonhurst. There are buildings for apartments and small houses. Most people are nice, but they are loud. Cars play loud music and drive fast. It can be noisy!

If you visit at night, be careful. Bensonhurst is safe, but people can be mean. You might meet people who want to fight or steal. I was bullied here once, but this was a long time ago.  People sometimes steal packages.

People do not always clean up after their dogs. You might see dog waste on the sidewalk.

Be careful and keep your shoes clean!

My house is at the top of a big hill.  People call it the “workout hill” because runners like to go up it. There are no sidewalks on my street, so people walk on the road. The road has holes and is hard to drive on. The telephone and electric wires look old and broken. It rains a lot here, so branches fall on the wires. The wires are fixed many times.

There are many tall trees around.  People do not like the trees. They want to cut them down. The trees block the view of the ocean.

Many houses are built high on the hill with big windows to see the bay. The sunset is pretty. The water shines and the sky is orange. It is often cloudy. 

Moss grows on everything.  My car turned green after I left it in the driveway for a month.

There are not many children here. There is a school nearby, but most people are old. People have dogs. They sit in yards or run down the street. Dogs sometimes go into houses.

Rabbits are everywhere. Gardeners do not like them because they dig in the ground. My cats like to hunt rabbits. We also see birds: small birds, hummingbirds, hawks, and eagles.  

There are no stores near my house. If you go down to the water, there are some restaurants. You can eat seafood. There is not much of a beach, but the rocks are fun to throw into the water. The bay is not wide. You can see the other side.

I live in a small town in Tennessee. My house is on a street that connects two big roads. There are many cars on the street. 

My neighborhood is quiet. Most people have lived here a long time. They take care of their yards and do normal things. In the winter, we go sledding down a small hill. Our house is at the corner. We see everyone driving by. 

We know most of the cars. If we see a car we do not know, we notice it. Some neighbors walk for exercise. Kids ride their bikes. It is normal. My wife and I work from home. We have two daughters, eleven and fourteen years old. We are home a lot. We play outside, even in the rain.

We often grill on our back deck. The smell is good. Many neighbors cut grass. We hear lawnmowers often from spring until fall. We have many trees in our neighborhood. It was a forest before houses were built. There are many leaves in the fall. We rake and burn them. I like the smell of burning leaves. It means fall has arrived.

We have not had much winter lately. It just feels like fall. Our garage is in the back. We do not use our front door much. I like to work in the garage. When the doors are open, I feel more connected to the neighborhood.

Holidays are quiet. Thanksgiving is busy. Many families visit. There are many cars. It is the same for Mother's Day and Christmas.

I like living here. If it were not a busy street, it would be perfect.

My neighborhood is in the center of the high desert. There is much dirt. People who have not lived here do not know how it feels to see only brown. If you see a green lawn, you know that person spends a lot of money on it. When I first lived here in the 1990s, houses were far apart. Now there are more houses. It looks more like a city each day. Most places are changing this way. Most people here are friendly. Like any city, there are good parts and bad parts. My neighborhood has many friendly older people. This makes it a good place to live. The stores are big chain stores like Food 4 Less and Smart & Final. If you want good food, you must travel. I do not see many Whole Foods stores here. Most jobs in this city are in construction. I think this is because the city is still growing. There is much empty space. This makes me worried. I like things as they are. I left a big city and do not want to go back. My job is in construction. I install drywall and T-bar. I like the animals in my home. People come to the high desert for many reasons. One reason is the beautiful desert. The desert climate and land have made special places that need protection. These places are home to many animals. People should learn about the animals to live together safely. My family and I live well with the animals. My three children love lizards and desert bugs.

Victorville has some attractions. It is good for families to experience the desert. They can have a different experience. You can visit the San Bernardino County Fair. The fair is fun for everyone. Visit Wrightwood nearby to see the snow-covered mountains. You can learn winter sports there.

The Victor Valley Museum has interesting things to see. There are rocks, old things, and objects from Native American people. These things show the history of Victorville.

My neighbor hood is different. I live on a college campus. My friends in the dorms are my neighbors. The campus is also my neighbor hood. It is like other neighbor hoods. It has houses, people, stores, and a park. 

Let's talk about the houses. There are three kinds: apartments, regular houses, and dorm rooms. Apartments have 2 to 4 people per room. There are 4 to 6 rooms per floor. Most apartments have 2 floors, so about 20 people live in each building. 

The regular houses are for rent. They have 2 to 4 bedrooms. Mostly older students live there. Dorm rooms are for students. Two students share a room. 

My school has many different kinds of people. Students, teachers, and staff live here. Older students live in apartments, newer students live in dorms, and staff live in the regular houses. 

There are many stores on campus. There are restaurants, shops, and grocery stores. You can get anything you need on campus. There is also a park. Everyone uses the park. It is safe and clean.

I have lived in my neighborhood for about ten years. When I first came here from Riverdale to Stockbridge, I felt sad. I missed my old friends and home. But my parents wanted a better life for me and my sister. Stockbridge had better houses and schools. It was a good move.

I made new friends and some enemies at school. I did not get to know my neighbors well, except for Mr. Glen and his children, and Dennis. They are good people. They feel like family. I remember going to Mr. Glen's wedding. It was fun and happy. I hope to have a wedding like that someday.

The neighborhood is like a maze. I use GPS to explore it. I have gone with my friends Kason and Curtis to the park. We played video games a lot and had fun. Sometimes I go to the park alone. Nature gives me peace. I also practice balancing with sticks from Home Depot and my wooden sword.

There is a basketball and tennis court, but I haven't played in a long time.

My dad taught me and my best friend to play tennis with Mr. Graves. We had a lot of fun, even when we worked hard.

I have had a lot of fun in this neighborhood. There are many good memories. I know there are more good times to come.

My house is near the college I go to. I like living there. There are many apartment buildings, with some restaurants and bars. The bars are not very expensive. One bar changed its name and is more expensive, but the drinks and service are good. The people there are nice. They are students or have low incomes. The apartments are not very expensive. There are many children nearby because there is a school close by. I do not know my neighbors. They smoke a lot of weed. The building managers put an air freshener near their door. It is funny. The buildings around me are old but may have new insides. 

Down the street are new apartments. I do not like them. They are cheaply built but expensive to rent. The rent is high because they are near the college. There is a cheap restaurant near me. They serve food on paper plates and most things are microwaved. Across from it is a gas station. People say it is not a good place to work. Last summer, the city put new sidewalks and grass on the road. It looks better. My apartment building is surrounded by trees. They cut down a few trees, but there are still many. Behind my building is a line of trees, and then more apartments.

I live on 42nd street. Behind me is 43rd street. It is not as nice. The sidewalks are bad, and the buildings look old. There are many trees there, maybe to hide the buildings. Most crime in the area happens at an apartment complex on 43rd street. But other apartments nearby also have crime. I like where I live. I can afford it, and it has what I need. I like that the college is walkable and there are bus stops close by.

My home is in a small area.  Many houses look alike. They are small buildings with two living areas. All the houses are yellow with white steps and green roofs. Most people living here know each other.  We often talk outside in the evenings. The children play together. It is good to be here.  It is quiet and peaceful. 

There are fields and trees around us. The sky is often blue with white clouds.  

This year, we had bad weather. There were warnings about tornadoes. One night, we heard loud alarms. We had to go to a safe place. I went to my bathroom with my small dog, my purse, and some pillows. My other dog stayed in the living room and was afraid.

There was a lot of hail. It made a loud noise when it hit the ground. After the storm, the road was hot and steam came up. The hail melted quickly. The sun came out and it started to rain. There was a long rainbow in the sky. I took pictures with my camera. I shared them with my friends and family.  They were happy to see them.

After the storm, people came back home. The children played again.

I like my neighborhood. It is nice to live here.

I live in a two-bedroom apartment. All the apartments look the same outside. But inside, they are different sizes. Some are small. 

I like to walk in the field behind my house. There is a small pond there. I have seen deer and frogs. It is a good place to live. It is near Charlotte.  Every morning, I hear roosters crowing. It is like living in a small town. There is even a donkey on a nearby farm. We can hear it make noise in the evening. I am glad I found this nice place to live.

I moved to this place when I was about to start eighth grade. It was hard to make friends at first. But I became close to two boys. One lives two houses away, and the other lives on my street. They do not live there now, but I still think about them. Most of the people who lived here when I first arrived are still here. My neighborhood is like most places in America. It has many two-story houses. On nice days, I hear kids playing outside. The neighborhood is quiet most days. I have never had a problem with anyone here. People here leave you alone unless you need help. I have ordered many things online, and no one has ever taken them from my porch. I trust my neighbors.

There is a park near my house. I have many memories there. I played basketball, football, and baseball with other boys. Once, I got hurt badly playing football, but the good times are better than the bad. Now, I go to the park with my cousins' kids. They are much younger than me and like to play on the swings and slides. Just thinking about the park makes them happy. The park makes me think about the past.

My neighborhood has many different kinds of people. There are many places to eat. In just one mile, you can find Chinese, Indian, Mexican, and Italian food. But many people order food using apps like GrubHub and DoorDash. Fast food places are popular, but you can find them anywhere. There are also many pizza places. The stores here have everything you need. There are dry cleaners, a Walgreens, a CVS, and a Jewel-Osco grocery store. There is even a store owned by an Indian family if you want to cook or buy Indian food.

I like my neighborhood. Reading about bad things that happen to people in other neighborhoods on social media makes me thankful for mine.

My town is small. It is in South Carolina. The town is known for peaches. It is called the Peach Capital of the World.  Most of the town is farms with peach trees and cows.  

The houses are far apart. They are two stories tall. Many have metal roofs. They are often far from the road.

There is one stop light in town.  There are a few stores there. There is a Chinese restaurant, a Mexican restaurant, and a small burger place. There used to be a pizza place, but it closed. There is a small drug store. They are known for their Cherry Coca-Cola. There is a grocery store called IGA. Many people go to a larger store in a nearby town for groceries. 

The most popular store is Dollar General. It sells many things. There is a furniture store and a pet groomer. There is a doctor and a veterinarian. There is one elementary school. Older students go to school in another town.

There are no parks in town, but they are building one. There are not many places to go in town.  There are no movie theaters or bowling alleys. It is a quiet town.

I first heard about my town on a show about missing people. It was strange. Most apartments cost more than one thousand dollars each month. I had not heard this story, and neither had my friends.  Maybe it is hard to live here. I know some friends feel sad at night. Things are expensive, but we have learned to save money. You like old toys from markets and clothes that are not new. You do not smell as much when you are older. You might smoke, or you just get used to things. But the market always feels important. The smell of being grown up is old magazines on a closed piano. It stays on your things even after you clean them.

There are three stores where you can buy used things within walking distance. If you start on one side, you can go to two stores that give money to good causes, a library, a store with old books, and a store with strange things. Downtown is busy. Cars and people fill the streets every day, but you cannot hear it in the stores. No matter how many people or cars go by, the store is quiet. It is a good place to spend an afternoon. Every year, there are more cars and people. It is a growing city, they say. It is the home of a very big company that sells things online and sends them to people. It is still growing, and it has problems. It reminds me of New York City. Everyone has their own goals, and no one asks much from you. You can be alone and quiet, and people leave you alone. It is not like the South, where people care a lot about each other. No one asks about your life here. You can hide as much as you want, and the city keeps moving like waves on the beach. It is a lively place to be.

Between the man who plays piano next door and the two people who sing badly upstairs, there is always something happening. We are more like a community of friends than a group of strangers. We help each other when we need to, we celebrate birthdays, we mourn deaths, and we look after each other. In a way, I am lucky to be here. I like most of my neighbors, and they are kind to me. I clean up after myself and share food with them, and they do the same. I bring them their mail, and they bring me mine. It is nice to see them, and I think they enjoy my company as much as I enjoy theirs. I live in a big, empty building, but people like my neighbors make me feel like I did not make a big mistake with my life.

My area is like most suburbs. The houses look the same. The homeowner's group keeps things neat.

The lawns are small and have flowers and rocks. There is a short drive way for each house. Every home has a two car garage. The roads are new and in good shape. There are no holes.

Most homes have one story, but some are two stories. We do not have mailboxes in front of each house. We have one big box for all the mail at the end of the street. People use a key to get to their mail. There are two big boxes for packages too.

My house is on the edge of the city. It feels like both the city and the country. There are many pools and trails. You can walk or run.

Most people here are older. The area is safe and everyone knows each other. There are some younger people here too. 

The city is big, but it feels small. We have stores and things we need. We have one mall. It is small, but good. It takes about fifteen minutes to drive to bigger stores. We have stores for all kinds of food, from fancy food to cheap food with few workers.

My neighborhood is safe and clean. It is like most suburbs. It has good things, but it is not special.

I live in a small town. The town is near a big city. My house is on the east side of town. This side is not rich. Homes here are small and often rented. But the people here are kind. They say hello when I see them. There is some crime here, like in any town. A few years ago, a man was shot near my home. My neighbors lost their son in a shooting.  Luckily, nothing bad has happened to my family.

Our town has been hurt by the drug problem. Many people have died. But there are good things here too. My son goes to a good school. The teachers are nice. He has friends and is happy there. 

The town has shops and places to go. We can get what we need. Our house is small, but it is home. We have lived here for a long time and like it here.

My neighborhood is full of culture. It is on a hill. There are old buildings there. I live in an apartment. It is seven stories tall. It is across from an old theater. Nearby is a small bar. Many people go there on warm nights.

There is a park near my house. It is big for this area. The park has walls. Steps go up the walls. In winter, homeless people live in tents near the park. They stay close together to keep warm. They are close to a center where they can wash up.

I like my city. I like the people. Hilltop was a bad place in the past. There were gangs. The police came to clean up the streets. People remember these days. They work hard to keep the area clean. They care about their city. Some people say that white people should not walk around at night. I think this is from the past.  

I think Hilltop sees me as one of them. I know about racism. I see it everywhere. I feel safe in my neighborhood. People are kind.

I feel alive here. I have met good people. They help each other. This is my home.

I live in a small town in Michigan. It is a place where farms meet small tourist places. There are no big city stores like malls or Wal-Mart. To go shopping, you must drive. 

My town is near two beautiful lakes: Lake Michigan and Lake Charlevoix. There are many beaches nearby. 

The houses in my neighborhood are not close together. They are old houses, some new and some old. Many have full basements. You can see the basements from the street. Many houses have aluminum siding. The houses are all different colors. Most have yards with things like trampolines and playsets. Some have gardens and fences for animals.

The people here are like people from all over Middle America. They work hard and raise families. You see children playing, people walking dogs, and people riding bikes. 

Everyone knows each other. You wave to your neighbors and smile at people you meet. The lawns are kept nice. There are no piles of leaves or overgrown bushes.

This neighborhood is not fancy, but it is a good place to raise a family. It is quiet, peaceful, and safe. It is a good place to come home to after a long day.

There is a sheriff’s office, jail, and health department nearby. The recycling center is close by too. There are baseball and softball fields where you can hear games. The town airport is nearby. You can hear planes taking off and landing.

You can walk to get ice cream. If you walk a little further, you can go downtown. My children can ride their bikes to the park. It is a great place to live.
